**Requirement**

- A dedicated error code to represent when a Workflow is trying to be scheduled when it is already running

---

Presently, the way to catch this error is with the following in .NET, which is not a great Dev Ex.

```c#
try
{
    result = await workflowClient.ScheduleNewWorkflowAsync(...);
}
catch(Grpc.Core.RpcException ex) when 
(ex.StatusCode == Grpc.Core.StatusCode.Unknown && ex.Status.Detail.Contains("an active workflow with ID"))
{ 
  ... 
}
```
